properties.fouling_epibionts_desc: Small chelonibia around neck and front flippers. Carapace clean.
Heavy barnacle load on soft tissue

properties.injury_desc: Symmetrical wounds found on both front flippers and head. Query netting entanglement.
V shaped cut on peduncle, and puncture wound that goes through peduncle (see screenshots attached from necropsy report).  Necropsy report on file at Manly marine parks.
properties.cod_cause_of_death_desc: No cause of death determined from necropsy. All pathology results came back negative.  Potential cause is old age (due to size, scarring and cataracts).  No evidence of recent meals.

properties.alive_and_rescued_notes: Turtle lethargic, somewhat reactive to people briefly, underweight, rub mark on back of head, sunken spots on front of carapace, slight flare on marginal scutes mid carapace, small barnacles but seem to be dieing off, mobile nodule right side of shoulder

properties.fouling_epibionts_desc: Barnacles most on the soft tissue area
properties.lumps_and_growths_desc: Small lump hanging off shell at rear near tail

properties.fouling_epibionts_desc: Small barnacles on soft tissue, none on carapace, some barnacles on plastron
